      "received_date": "2024-12-12",
      "received_method": "fax",
      "content": {
        "format": "text",
        "text_content": "FAX TRANSMISSION\nFROM: LAKESIDE PRIMARY CARE\nTO: MONTZKA EYE CLINIC\nPAGES: 1 of 1\nDATE: 12/12/2024 11:47\n\nLAKESIDE PRIMARY CARE\nDaniel Reyes, MD - Internal Medicine\n740 Lakeside Commons Blvd, Suite 110\nOrlando, FL 32812\nPhone: (407) 555-9010 | Fax: (407) 555-9011 | NPI: 1435792860\n\nDate: December 12, 2024\n\nRE: REFERRAL FOR ANNUAL DIABETIC EYE EXAMINATION\n\nPatient Name: Robert M. Alvarez\nDate of Birth: 09/05/1962 (62 years old)\nMedical Record #: LPC-2016-3308\nPhone: (407) 555-8142\n\nDear Colleague,\n\nI am referring Mr. Robert Alvarez for his annual dilated diabetic eye examination.\n\nCLINICAL CONTEXT:\n62-year-old male with type 2 diabetes mellitus, diagnosed 2016. Most recent hemoglobin A1c 7.2% (November 2024). Blood pressure well controlled on lisinopril. Your office performed his diabetic eye examination last December and found mild nonproliferative diabetic retinopathy in both eyes; he was asked to return in twelve months.\n\nHe reports no blurred vision, floaters, flashes, or other visual complaints.\n\nCURRENT MEDICATIONS:\n1. Metformin 1000mg PO twice daily\n2. Lisinopril 20mg PO daily\n\nALLERGIES: Penicillin - hives with amoxicillin as a child.\n\nRECENT VITALS (from 12/09/2024 visit):\nBP: 126/78 | HR: 70 | BMI: 29.4\n\nREQUEST:\nAnnual dilated fundus examination and OCT for diabetic retinopathy surveillance. Please forward your report to my attention.\n\nSincerely,\n\nDaniel Reyes, MD\nLakeside Primary Care\nFL Medical License: ME778901\n\n[End of fax transmission]",
