      "content": {
        "format": "text",
        "text_content": "MONTZKA EYE CLINIC - OFFICE VISIT NOTE\n\nPatient: Robert M. Alvarez\nDOB: 09/05/1962\nMRN: MEC-2023-0642\nDate of Service: December 5, 2023\nVisit Type: Established Patient - Diabetic Eye Examination\nProvider: Elena Montzka, MD\n\nCHIEF COMPLAINT:\nAnnual diabetic eye examination. No visual complaints.\n\nHISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS:\nMr. Alvarez is a 61-year-old man with type 2 diabetes mellitus diagnosed in 2016, referred by his primary care physician for annual diabetic retinopathy surveillance. He denies blurred vision, floaters, flashes, or eye pain.\n\nEXAMINATION:\nVisual acuity (corrected): OD 20/20, OS 20/20\nIntraocular pressure (applanation): OD 15 mmHg, OS 16 mmHg\nDilated fundus examination: Scattered microaneurysms and rare dot hemorrhages in the posterior pole of each eye. No hard exudates, cotton wool spots, venous beading, or neovascularization. Maculae flat with normal foveal reflex.\n\nIMAGING:\nMacular OCT both eyes: normal foveal contour, no intraretinal or subretinal fluid, no macular edema. Central subfield thickness within normal limits.\n\nASSESSMENT:\n1. Mild nonproliferative diabetic retinopathy, both eyes (E11.3293) - scattered microaneurysms, no macular edema.\n2. Type 2 diabetes mellitus - continue medical management with primary care.\n\nPLAN:\n1. Continue current medical management; encouraged glycemic and blood pressure control.\n2. Return in twelve months for repeat dilated examination and macular OCT, sooner for any new floaters, vision change, or distortion.\n\n[ELECTRONIC SIGNATURE APPLIED]\nElena Montzka, MD\nDictated: 12/05/2023 15:20 | Signed: 12/05/2023 15:41"
      },
